    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="535"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.12/23</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-30">August 30,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1562</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No.
                    3387 dated July 23, 1930, concerning the cases of persons of both American and
                    Brazilian nationalities who desire to have their American passports visaed to
                    enable them to leave Brazil.</p>
                <p>You are informed that the American consular officers in Brazil are being
                    instructed to take up all such cases with the Embassy in the future instead of
                    taking them up with the local police authorities.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castle, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
